make sure that configure correctly determines whether -liconv is required

iconv_open is a symbol that's can also be provided by glibc,
but other symbols like libiconv_open are not,
which leads to linking errors like "undefined reference to libiconv_open"

based on fix for very similar problem discussed in https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/issues/6239,
see https://github.com/FirebirdSQL/firebird/commit/9d1d37b389d20824a0d5d8c3cee7e6c518c32304

author: Kenneth Hoste (HPC-UGent)

--- gnuplot-6.0.3/configure.ac.orig	2026-06-10 22:22:50.301034482 +0200
+++ gnuplot-6.0.3/configure.ac	2026-06-10 22:23:23.236831265 +0200
@@ -609,7 +609,7 @@
 
 dnl The iconv library can be used to switch character encodings.
 dnl So far this is only used by gd.trm and emf.trm.
-AC_SEARCH_LIBS([iconv_open], [iconv],
+AC_SEARCH_LIBS([libiconv_open], [iconv],
   [AC_CHECK_HEADER([iconv.h],
     [AC_DEFINE([HAVE_ICONV], 1, [define if you have libiconv and iconv.h])]
   )]
